The paper discusses the application of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to clinical time-series data for patient risk stratification. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and clinical engineering (cs.CE). Given the focus on RNNs and their use in patient risk stratification, it is most likely that the paper belongs to cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE. The use of synthetic data and the comparison of different RNN architectures may also suggest a focus on experimental design and evaluation, which could further support the classification of the paper under cs.LG.
